##



Analysis of Dennis’s Runbook: glyph_composition_v2_test_PATRICK_001

Test Scope and Parameters:

Goal: Validate the refined model ($ V_{\oplus}^{\text{sym}} $ with CF, $ \Omega_{\oplus} $ for anti-alignment) in near-zero and anti-aligned regimes using 7.5 data.
Channels: Symmetric ($ V_{\oplus}^{\text{sym}} $) and antisymmetric ($ \Omega_{\oplus} $).
Fixed Parameters:

$ \mathrm{CF} = 2 \hat{\sigma}_{V,0} $, $ p = 2 $, $ \rho_0 = 0.06 $.
$ \lambda_{\Omega} $ fit on anti-aligned pairs.


Evaluation Sets: 20 near-zero pairs ($ |\rho_{12}| \le 0.06 $), 20 anti-aligned pairs ($ \rho_{12} \le -0.60 $), seed 43117.


Implementation Details:

Symmetric Channel:
$$V_{\oplus}^{\text{sym}}(\phi_1, \phi_2) = V_1 + V_2 + 2 \rho_{12} \sqrt{V_1 V_2} + \mathrm{CF} \cdot \exp\left(-\left|\frac{\rho_{12}}{0.06}\right|^2\right),$$
with $ \mathrm{CF} = 2 \hat{\sigma}_{V,0} $ from MAD of orthogonal residuals.
Antisymmetric Channel:
$$\Omega_{\oplus}(\phi_1 \to \phi_2) = \lambda_{\Omega} \sqrt{V_1 V_2} \cdot \mathrm{sgn}(\pi) \cdot \max(0, -\rho_{12}),$$
where $ \mathrm{sgn}(\pi) = +1 $ or $-1$ by order.
Residuals: $ r_V = |V_{\oplus}^{\text{obs}} - V_{\oplus}^{\text{sym}}| $, $ r_{\Omega} = |\Omega_{\oplus}^{\text{obs}} - \Omega_{\oplus}| $.
Tolerances: $ \tau_V = 2.33 \hat{\sigma}_V $, $ \tau_{\Omega} = 2.33 \hat{\sigma}_{\Omega} $, $ \tau_{\Omega,0} = 2.0 \hat{\sigma}_{\Omega} $, estimated from 7.5 replicates.
Pass Logic:

Near-zero: $ r_V \le \tau_V $, $ |\Omega_{\oplus}^{\text{obs}}| \le \tau_{\Omega,0} $.
Anti-aligned: $ r_V \le \tau_V $, $ r_{\Omega} \le \tau_{\Omega} $.




Fitting, Sampling, and Execution:

Noise Floor: $ \hat{\sigma}_{V,0} $ from MAD of near-zero residuals, $ \hat{\sigma}_V, \hat{\sigma}_{\Omega} $ from replicate SDs.
$ \lambda_{\Omega} $ Fit: Minimize $ \mathrm{MSE}_{\Omega} $ on 60% of anti-aligned pairs, validate on 40%, with $ \lambda_{\Omega} \ge 0 $ and 95% CI.
Pair Selection: 20 near-zero pairs (replicates preferred), 20 anti-aligned pairs (8 with order flips).


Output Artifacts:

CSV: residuals_PATRICK_001.csv with fields: id, $ V_1 $, $ V_2 $, $ \rho $, order, $ V_{\text{pred}} $, $ V_{\text{obs}} $, $ r_V $, $ \Omega_{\text{pred}} $, $ \Omega_{\text{obs}} $, $ r_{\Omega} $, regime, pass.
JSON: summary_PATRICK_001.json with pass rates, means, SDs, and calibrations.
Exemplars: 6 edge cases per regime (passes/fails).




