Notes on the YAML

Structure: Nested under glyph_pairs to match Dennis’s glyph_composition_v2_test_PATRICK_001 schema, with each pair as a YAML object.
Field Replication: Uses exact field names from the protocol (e.g., V_1, rho, Omega_pred) for seamless integration.
Data Generation: Values are simulated based on Dennis’s mock ranges ($ V_1, V_2 \in [0.5, 2] $, $ \rho_{12} $ per regime), with noise $ \epsilon \sim \mathcal{N}(0, 0.001) $ and $ \Omega_{\text{pred}} $ derived from $ \lambda_{\Omega} \approx 1 $ (placeholder until fitted).
Regime Assignment: Near-zero (1–10), anti-aligned with both orders (11–30) to test antisymmetry.





